---
title: "Section Generation Sequence - BCE V2.1 (12-Layer Context Assembly)"
---
sequenceDiagram
    participant UI as SvelteKit UI
    participant API as API Route
    participant PA as Prompt Assembler
    participant DB as SQLite (25+ tables)
    participant CLI as Claude CLI (claude -p)
    participant User as Operator

    UI->>API: Generate section (section_spec_id)
    API->>PA: Assemble context for section

    Note over PA,DB: 12-Layer Context Assembly

    PA->>DB: L1: Platform constraints
    PA->>DB: L2: brand_profiles (voice, tone)
    PA->>DB: L3: brand_rules (filtered by scope)
    Note right of DB: global -> page_type -> section_type
    PA->>DB: L4: section_specs (from blueprint)
    PA->>DB: L5: Page-level SEO requirements
    PA->>DB: L6: internal_link_graph + anchor_text_bank
    PA->>DB: L7: GEO requirements (direct answer, stats)
    PA->>DB: L8: css_audit (tiered class palette)
    PA->>DB: L9: Previously generated sections (this page)
    PA->>DB: L10: brand_examples (few-shot approved)
    PA->>DB: L11: Suburb/location data (if applicable)
    PA->>DB: L12: Output format instructions

    DB-->>PA: All 12 layers (~3,000-8,500 tokens)
    PA-->>API: Assembled prompt

    API->>CLI: Pipe prompt via stdin
    Note right of CLI: Timeout: 120s<br/>Retries: 3x exponential

    CLI-->>API: Generated HTML section

    API->>API: Validate output
    Note right of API: CSS class check<br/>HTML well-formedness<br/>Link presence<br/>Word count range<br/>No placeholders

    alt Validation passes
        API->>DB: Store in section_specs.generated_html
        API-->>UI: Show section for review
        UI->>User: Present generated section

        alt User approves
            User->>UI: Approve
            UI->>API: Mark approved
            API->>DB: section_specs.status = approved
            API->>DB: Store in brand_examples (positive)
            API->>DB: Update brand_rules (confidence++)
        else User requests refinement
            User->>UI: Feedback + refinement request
            UI->>API: Store feedback, regenerate
            API->>DB: Store feedback in section_specs.last_feedback
            API->>DB: Create brand_rule (source=feedback, scope=relevant)
            API->>PA: Re-assemble with feedback as additional context
            PA->>CLI: Regenerate with feedback
        else User rejects
            User->>UI: Reject with reason
            UI->>API: Mark rejected
            API->>DB: section_specs.status = rejected
            API->>DB: Store in brand_examples (is_negative=1)
            API->>DB: Create anti-pattern brand_rule
        end
    else Validation fails
        API->>API: Retry (up to 3 attempts)
    end
